    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
      <img src="https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/1996950534-ab58c31114f162230baa21d656052dbd1f673936bd3e796469e75afa266991bb-d_960?region=us" alt="Product Video: How to Turn Features into Sales" loading="eager" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin:8px 0 26px;aspect-ratio:16/9;object-fit:cover" />

      <h2>From features to desire</h2>
      <p>"2,000-watt motor" doesn't sell. "Ready in half the time, every morning" does. The product video that works translates the technical into a concrete benefit, and shows it in action so the viewer can picture themselves using it. That jump — from spec sheet to feeling — is what actually moves a purchase.</p>

      <h2>Less friction, more conversion</h2>
      <p>In e-commerce, product video is one of the biggest conversion drivers: it answers questions before they come up, reduces returns, and gives the buyer the confidence to click. A product that's understood in 30 seconds sells better than one that has to be decoded.</p>

      <h2>Shorten the sales cycle</h2>
      <p>In B2B sales, a good product video does part of the sales team's job: it explains the complex simply, aligns everyone involved in the decision, and speeds up the "yes." A film can travel through an organization far faster than a meeting can.</p>

      <h2>Brands that trust us</h2>
      <p>We've produced product films for V-ZUG, ON and Franke that turn features into desire — and clicks into buyers. Each one shot with cinema-level craft and a focus on the business outcome.</p>

      <p>See our <a href="/en/services/product-video/">product video</a> work, or <a href="/en/contact/">tell us about your product</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
